	                                <p>Hi Jan!</p><p>Sorry for my late response :). Of course, an OAuth server can choose to do anything, but I do *not* believe that the implicit grant type should have the ability to give you a refresh token. And that makes sense - if with this grant type, you have the client secret, so you can just go get a new access token whenever you want (making it unnecessary to use the refresh token).</p><p>I hope that helps!</p>
